	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-03-29T23:40:36">Sovereign Mines of Africa Plc is a United Kingdom-based holding company. The principal activity of the Company is the exploration of gold concessions in the Republic of Guinea. Its Mandiana-Magana gold project, which is located in Mandiana Province, northeast Guinea, and covers an area of approximately 127 square kilometer (sq km). The Companys other projects include Dalaghna and Marela gold project. The Dalaghna gold project is located approximately near south of the town of Kankan in eastern Guinea and covers an area of approximately 500 sq km. The Marela gold project is located near southeast of the regional center of Mamou in south central Guinea on the border with Sierra Leone and covers an area totaling approximately 736 sq km. The Companys subsidiaries include Sovereign Mines of Africa Ltd., Sovereign Mines of Guinea Ltd. and Guiord SA.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2016-02-07T20:30:47">BRIEF: For the six months ended 30 June 2015, Sovereign Mines of Africa PLC revenues was not reported. Net loss decreased 45% to L47K. Lower net loss reflects Other administrative expenses decrease of 43% to L47K (expense), Losses on financial assets at fair value decrease from L2K (expense) to L0K.</Text>
